---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects | Learn Web Design With Quinton Jason">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Projects</p>
        <h1>Class projects and checkpoints.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A practical path through the course work: setup, structure, styling,
          layout, interaction, motion, media, navigation, and accessibility.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="project-list">
        <article class="project-card">
          <p class="project-card__meta">Project 1 / Setup and publishing</p>
          <h2>Launch a starter website</h2>
          <p>
            Set up GitHub, GitHub Desktop, VS Code, a starter repository, and a
            live GitHub Pages URL.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Working local project folder</li>
            <li>Published repository</li>
            <li>Live site URL</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="project-card__links">
            <a href="/lessons/developer-environment-setup/">Developer Environment Setup</a>
            <a href="/lessons/file-paths-and-site-structure/">File Paths and Site Structure</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-card">
          <p class="project-card__meta">Project 2 / HTML foundation</p>
          <h2>Build a small multi-page site</h2>
          <p>
            Create a simple site with meaningful page structure, headings,
            paragraphs, images, lists, internal links, and external links.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Home page</li>
            <li>About or contact page</li>
            <li>Correct relative paths</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="project-card__links">
            <a href="/lessons/basic-html-structure-and-elements/">HTML Structure and Elements</a>
            <a href="/lessons/intro-to-css/">Intro to CSS</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-card">
          <p class="project-card__meta">Project 3 / Visual system</p>
          <h2>Design and style a complete page</h2>
          <p>
            Apply typography, spacing, color, box model decisions, and layout
            systems so the page feels intentional instead of default.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>External stylesheet</li>
            <li>Readable type scale</li>
            <li>Flexbox or grid layout</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="project-card__links">
            <a href="/lessons/styling-text-with-css/">Styling Text with CSS</a>
            <a href="/lessons/box-model-and-layout/">Box Model and Layout</a>
            <a href="/lessons/flexbox/">Flexbox</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-card">
          <p class="project-card__meta">Project 4 / Responsive interaction</p>
          <h2>Add navigation and JavaScript behavior</h2>
          <p>
            Build responsive navigation and small DOM interactions while keeping
            controls semantic, keyboard friendly, and understandable.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Responsive layout adjustments</li>
            <li>Navigation pattern</li>
            <li>DOM interaction</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="project-card__links">
            <a href="/lessons/responsive-web-design/">Responsive Web Design</a>
            <a href="/lessons/javascript-in-the-dom/">JavaScript in the DOM</a>
            <a href="/lessons/building-effective-site-navigation/">Effective Site Navigation</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-card">
          <p class="project-card__meta">Project 5 / Polish and accessibility</p>
          <h2>Refine motion, media, and accessibility</h2>
          <p>
            Add thoughtful transitions, animation, optimized images, carousel
            behavior, and an accessibility pass before final presentation.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Motion that respects reduced motion</li>
            <li>Optimized images and media</li>
            <li>Keyboard and contrast testing</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="project-card__links">
            <a href="/lessons/css-transitions/">CSS Transitions</a>
            <a href="/lessons/css-animation/">CSS Animation</a>
            <a href="/lessons/image-optimization/">Image Optimization</a>
            <a href="/lessons/mastering-carousels/">Mastering Carousels</a>
            <a href="/lessons/web-accessibility/">Web Accessibility</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
